# Bayesian Estimation of a Dynamic Linear Regression (Unemployment)
*Home Assignment — Econometrics III (WS 2024/25)*

> My solution for the Econometrics III home assignment. 
> I estimate a dynamic linear regression for U.S. unemployment with a Normal–Gamma prior,
> Gibbs sampling, regime-dependent precision (calm vs. recession), and a simple forecast.

---

## Overview
We model monthly unemployment (`UNEMP`) with distributed lags of industrial production (`INPRO`), CPI (`CPI`), business confidence (`BCONF`), and a COVID dummy:

